<figureCitation id="131BEC90387FFFD1FBF9FA2F2FC0000D" box="[1101,1178,1525,1549]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="57.[129,168,1779,1803]" captionTargetBox="[128,1451,1049,1763]" captionTargetId="figure@57.[128,1451,1049,1763]" captionTargetPageId="57" captionText="Fig. 17. a. Brachyhypopomus gauderio, NUP 2510, 112.2, lagoa do Aurélio, Taquarussu, State of Mato Grosso do Sul. b. Gymnorhamphichthys britskii, NUP 3337, 115.0 mm TL, rio Baía, Taquarussu, State of Mato Grosso do Sul. c. Rhamphichthys hahni, 567.3 mm TL, uncat. d. Eigenmannia guairaca, NUP 16151, 112.3 mm TL, córrego Água Boa, tributary of the rio Iguatemi, Mundo Novo, Mato Grosso do Sul State. e. Eigenmannia trilineata, 109.2 mm TL, fresh specimen, uncat. f. Eigenmannia virescens, 205.0 mm TL, uncat. g. Sternopygus macrurus, NUP 2096, 280.0 mm TL, rio Paraná, Porto Rico, State of Paraná." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3678431" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3678431/files/figure.png" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">
<emphasis id="B9542C07387FFFD1FBF9FA2F2FC0000D" bold="true" box="[1101,1178,1525,1549]" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">Fig. 17</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C33AA39E387FFFD0FCEEF9EF295A06C7" lastPageId="57" lastPageNumber="58" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B9FF015387FFFD1FCEEF9EF2E4201AD" blockId="56.[820,1460,1589,1965]" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">
Body elongated and compressed; greatest depth contained 5.8 to 8.1 times in TL; head length 7.6 to 8.6, anal-fin base length 1.2 to 1.4, caudal-peduncle length 2.0 to 3.1, preanal distance 3.9 to 5.0 and prepectoral distance 7.0 to 
<quantity id="4CD85DF0387FFFD1FAC6F94C2EE900AD" box="[1394,1459,1685,1710]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0066" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" unit="in" value="7.9">7.9 in</quantity>
LEA; snout length 2.4 to 4.3, horizontal orbital diameter 8.2 to 11.1 and least interorbital width 
<quantity id="4CD85DF0387FFFD1FB1BF90C2E6900ED" box="[1199,1331,1749,1774]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0287" metricValueMax="1.2192" metricValueMin="0.8382" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" unit="in" value="4.05" valueMax="4.8" valueMin="3.3">3.3 to 4.8 in</quantity>
HL. Mouth terminal. Pectoral fin with 14-17 rays and anal fin with 179- 226 rays; transverse series above lateral line with 7-8 scale rows (
<bibRefCitation id="EFB18DE4387FFFD1FCC9F8EC2FDE014E" author="Graca, Pavanelli" box="[893,1156,1845,1870]" firstAuthor="Graca" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" pagination="58 - 64" refId="ref84115" refString="Pavanelli CS, Graca WJ, Zawadzki CH, Britski HA, Vidotti AP, Avelino GS, Verissimo S. Fishes from the Corumba Reservoir, Paranaiba River drainage, upper rio Parana basin, State of Goias, Brazil. Check List. 2007; 3 (1): 58 - 64." type="journal article" year="2007">Graça, Pavanelli, 2007</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB18DE4387FFFD1FB22F8EF2EF2014E" author="Giora, Malabarba" box="[1174,1448,1845,1870]" firstAuthor="Giora" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" pagination="60 - 68" refId="ref81141" refString="Giora J, Malabarba LR. Brachyhypopomus gauderio, new species, a new example of underestimated species diversity of electric fishes in the southern South America (Gymnotiformes: Hypopomidae). Zootaxa. 2009; 2093: 60 - 68." type="journal article" year="2009">Giora, Malabarba, 2009</bibRefCitation>
). Ground color yellowish to pale brown; dorsal region and lower-half of body with dark-brown transverse and irregular bars; anal fin hyaline, with dark-brown spots.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9FF015387EFFD0FF35FF6A295A06C7" blockId="57.[129,512,176,200]" box="[129,512,176,200]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">
<emphasis id="B9542C07387EFFD0FF35FF6A2ADC06C8" bold="true" box="[129,390,176,200]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Maximum total length.</emphasis>
160.0 mm.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C33AA39E387EFFD0FF35FF2A2A3D0728" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8B9FF015387EFFD0FF35FF2A2A3D0728" blockId="57.[129,768,240,296]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">
<emphasis id="B9542C07387EFFD0FF35FF2A2A490708" bold="true" box="[129,275,240,264]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Distribution.</emphasis>
Río de basin, Laguna dos Patos and rio Tramandaí drainages.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C33AA39E387EFFD0FF35FE8B2BAC0449" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B9FF015387EFFD0FF35FE8B2BAC0449" blockId="57.[129,768,337,585]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">
<emphasis id="B9542C07387EFFD0FF35FE8B2BB50769" bold="true" box="[129,239,337,361]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C208B96387EFFD0FF49FE8B296B0769" authorityName="Giora, Malabarba" authorityYear="2009" box="[253,561,337,361]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Hypopomidae" genus="Brachyhypopomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Gymnotiformes" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="gauderio">
<emphasis id="B9542C07387EFFD0FF49FE8B296B0769" box="[253,561,337,361]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Brachyhypopomus gauderio</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was identified as 
<taxonomicName id="4C208B96387EFFD0FF35FEA82A3F0789" baseAuthorityName="Hopkins, Comfort, Bastian, Bass" baseAuthorityYear="1990" box="[129,357,369,393]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Hypopomidae" genus="Brachyhypopomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Gymnotiformes" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pinnicaudatus">
<emphasis id="B9542C07387EFFD0FF35FEA82BC20789" box="[129,152,370,393]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">B.</emphasis>
cf. 
<emphasis id="B9542C07387EFFD0FF7AFEAB2A3F0789" box="[206,357,369,393]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">pinnicaudatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB18DE4387EFFD0FE2FFEAB29F10789" author="Graca, Pavanelli" box="[411,683,369,393]" firstAuthor="Graca" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" pagination="58 - 64" refId="ref84115" refString="Pavanelli CS, Graca WJ, Zawadzki CH, Britski HA, Vidotti AP, Avelino GS, Verissimo S. Fishes from the Corumba Reservoir, Paranaiba River drainage, upper rio Parana basin, State of Goias, Brazil. Check List. 2007; 3 (1): 58 - 64." type="journal article" year="2007">Graça, Pavanelli (2007)</bibRefCitation>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB18DE4387EFFD0FD08FEAB2A6707A9" author="Giora, Malabarba" firstAuthor="Giora" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" pagination="60 - 68" refId="ref81141" refString="Giora J, Malabarba LR. Brachyhypopomus gauderio, new species, a new example of underestimated species diversity of electric fishes in the southern South America (Gymnotiformes: Hypopomidae). Zootaxa. 2009; 2093: 60 - 68." type="journal article" year="2009">Giora, Malabarba (2009)</bibRefCitation>
described the new species from the Laguna dos Patos and rio Tramandaí drainages, río 
<collectingCountry id="F337B085387EFFD0FDFFFE6B29F407C9" box="[587,686,433,457]" name="Paraguay" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Paraguay</collectingCountry>
and río 
<collectingCountry id="F337B085387EFFD0FF35FE0B2B8407E9" box="[129,222,465,489]" name="Uruguay" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Uruguay</collectingCountry>
basins. 
<taxonomicName id="4C208B96387EFFD0FE86FE0B290407E9" authorityName="Giora, Malabarba" authorityYear="2009" box="[306,606,465,489]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Hypopomidae" genus="Brachyhypopomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Gymnotiformes" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="gauderio">
<emphasis id="B9542C07387EFFD0FE86FE0B290407E9" box="[306,606,465,489]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Brachyhypopomus gauderio</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a non-native species from the upper rio Paraná, and its occurrence in the region can be associated with its introduction as a live bait by anglers.
</paragraph>
